definition.value: A glycosylmannose that is beta-D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-mannopyranoside.
An amino disaccharide that is that is the 3-O-beta-D-galactopyranoside of 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-galactopyranose.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of two beta-D-galactofuranosyl residues joined by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A galactotriose that is beta-D-galatopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 6 have been glycosylated by alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residues.

An amino tetrasaccharide that is beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->3)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 6 f the acetamidogalactopyranose group has been glycosylated by a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-4-O-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A mannotetarose consisting of three alpha-D-mannopyranose residues and a D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by (1->2), (1->2) and (1->3) glycosidic bonds.

An amino tetrasaccharide that is alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the beta-D-galactopyranosyl moiety has been glycosylated by an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl group.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residues joine in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucopyranosyl, beta-D-galactopyranosyl and alpha-D-mannopyranosyl residues joined in sequence by (1->3) and (1->4) glycosidic linkages.
